				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I really enjoyed this story, the tone is perfect and makes the description of the suicide fascinating &#8211; just cold and clinical enough to distance you, with little teasers of emotion that suddenly trigger emotion (his mind is elsewhere).</p>
<p>I loved the tone, the itallics made it more cold and clinical, the underlying story is touching, and &#8211; good name. Troy Packham is an excellent name, and using the full name-and-surname really works in terms of that clinical vibe again.</p>
<p>I really liked it and thought is was very successful.</p>
